help.1: Total gross revenue for the calendar billing period, calculated by summing 'Needs your approval', 'Approved', 'Pending Payment', and 'Paid'. All values are prior to Dynasty deduction of applicable fees.
help.2: Percentage change in total gross revenue from previous calendar billing period.
help.3:
Outstanding (or waived/exempted) billing in calendar billing period.

  • Needs your approval: Billing items that need firm approval before Dynasty can debit/credit accounts.
  • Approved: Billing items approved for debiting/crediting, but not yet debited/credited at custodian.
  • Waived/Exempted: Only advisory fees can be waived/exempted. Program, Manager, and Core fees cannot be exempted and removed from billing file.
help.4:
Status of billing in process of debiting/crediting.

  • Pending payment: Fees that are pending processing at the custodian (e.g., creating custodian extracts, pending at custodian, waiting on rejections)
  • Paid: Fees processed at the custodian and sent to Dynasty Finance for net payment (debis/credits).
  • Rejected: Fees that have not been processed at the custodian due to various reasons and require further action.
help.5: Quarter over quarter on-cycle trend analysis, depicting current quarter along with the previous 4 quarters.
help.6:
Quarter over quarter adjustment billing trend analysis, broken out by billing type:

  • New Accounts/Contributions: Includes contributions > $50k threshold, new account billing, and reactivation of accounts.
  • Terminations/Withdrawals: Includes withdrawals > $50k threshold and termination of accounts from billing.
  • Adjustments Includes any fee changes or program changes.
help.7: Total client advisory fees for the household in selected calendar billing period, calculated by summing billing from on-cycle, new accounts, deposits, and net positive adjustments and reducing by any credits for withdrawals, terminations, and net negative adjustments. All values are prior to Dynasty deduction of applicable fees.
help.8: Account-level breakdown for the household, showing client advisory fee information (fees, total and excluded assets, and annualized effective rates) related to the selected calendar billing period.
help.9: Account Market Value for the day of the flow
help.10: Fee Amount Variance compares the fee amount of the displayed fee to the prior Periodic, Inception, or Reassignment fee.  If no prior fee is available, the variance will be 100%.
help.11: Fee AUM Variance compares the billable market value of the displayed fee to the prior Periodic, Inception, or Reassignment fee.  If no prior fee is available, the variance will be 100%.
